Definition.WordDefinition: November \No*vem"ber\, n. [L. November, or Novembris (sc. mensis), the ninth month of the old Roman year, which began with March, fr. novem nine: cf. F. Novembre. See {Nine}.] The eleventh month of the year, containing thirty days. [1913 Webster]
November n : the month following October and preceding December [syn: {Nov}]
